  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Our method surpasses all baselines on four datasets regarding best F1 by 6.45%, 0.98%, 14.14% and 0.31%.",
    "In terms of delay F1, our method outperforms all baselines on four datasets by 4.98%, 1.58%, 38.68% and 0.65%.",
    "The performance of various baseline methods on the datasets exhibits considerable variation.",
    "For instance, SPOT [42] does not excel on most datasets, as it erroneously treats extreme values as anomalies, whereas anomalies are not always manifested as such.",
    "SRCNN [38] is a reasonably proficient classifier, yet its performance falls short compared to most other models."
  ],
